_id>59083</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers and Jayhawks to Step Into the National Spotlight For Key Weekend Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/6/baseball-mountaineers-and-jayhawks-to-step-into-the-national-spotlight-for-key-weekend-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/6/baseball-mountaineers-and-jayhawks-to-step-into-the-national-spotlight-for-key-weekend-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia University baseball coach Steve Sabins celebrates his team's 7-2 victory over Marshall at GoMart Ballpark in Charleston, W.Va., on Tuesday, May 5, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/6/Sabins-Main_3uchU.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – There will be lots of eyes watching the ESPN+ broadcasts of West Virginia's Big 12 Conference series at Kansas this weekend.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/6/Sabins-Main_3uchU.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/6/Sabins-Main_3uchU.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia University baseball coach Steve Sabins celebrates his team's 7-2 victory over Marshall at GoMart Ballpark in Charleston, W.Va., on Tuesday, May 5, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/6/Sabins-Main_3uchU.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 6 May 2026 12:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59082</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Handle Marshall in Charleston</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/baseball-mountaineers-handle-marshall-in-charleston</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/baseball-mountaineers-handle-marshall-in-charleston</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Marshall at GoMart Ballpark in Charleston, W.Va., on Tuesday, May 5, 2026." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/5/EEN02319_Z6nAx.jpeg" /><br /><br />CHARLESTON, W.Va. – The No. 15 West Virginia University baseball team completed the season sweep of Marshall with a 7-2 victory at GoMart Ballpark, Tuesday night in the state capital. The Mountaineers improve to 32-12 while the Thundering Herd fall to 21-27.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/5/EEN02319_Z6nAx.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/5/EEN02319_Z6nAx.jpeg"><media:title>Gavin Kelly rounds the bases after hitting a home run against Marshall at GoMart Ballpark in Charleston, W.Va., on Tuesday, May 5, 2026.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/5/EEN02319_Z6nAx.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 5 May 2026 22:39:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59081</s:story_id></item><item><title>WVU Posts 991 APR Score</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/general-wvu-posts-991-apr-score</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/general-wvu-posts-991-apr-score</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Woodburn Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2022/3/30/Woodburn_033022.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University's varsity athletic teams have a combined Academic Progress Rate (APR) score of 991 according to data released today by the NCAA. The 991 score matches WVU's highest score for the 22 years of the NCAA Academic Performance Program.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2022/3/30/Woodburn_033022.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2022/3/30/Woodburn_033022.jpg"><media:title>Woodburn Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2022/3/30/Woodburn_033022.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 5 May 2026 13:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59079</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Working To Flip The Script for 2026</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/football-mountaineers-working-to-flip-the-script-for-2025</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/5/football-mountaineers-working-to-flip-the-script-for-2025</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Head coach Rich Rodriguez looks on as the Mountaineers prepare for their game against Ohio in Athens, Ohio, on Sept. 6, 2025." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/9/6/9.6.25LH-7713_toWoP.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – A few weeks ago, Travis Trickett, one of coach Rich Rodriguez's right-hand men as West Virginia's senior offensive assistant coach, talked about the Big 12 Conference being considered one of college football's &quot;flip leagues.&quot;]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/9/6/9.6.25LH-7713_toWoP.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvuspo