/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/4/EEN09358_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore pitcher Chansen Cole of the West Virginia University baseball team has been named Big 12 Newcomer of the Week, as announced by the league on Monday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/EEN09358_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/EEN09358_large.jpg"><media:title>Chansen Cole</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/EEN09358_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 4 May 2026 16:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59076</s:story_id></item><item><title>Cole Named Student-Athlete of the Week</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/4/baseball-cole-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/4/baseball-cole-named-student-athlete-of-the-week</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Chansen Cole pitching" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/4/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-08535.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore pitcher Chansen Cole of the West Virginia University baseball team has been named the WVU Student-Athlete of the Week, presented by University Apartments.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-08535.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-08535.jpg"><media:title>Chansen Cole pitching</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/4/20260421_BASE_WVUvsPitt_TT-08535.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 4 May 2026 12:09:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59075</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Completes Sweep of Kansas State</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/3/baseball-west-virginia-completes-sweep-of-kansas-state</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/3/baseball-west-virginia-completes-sweep-of-kansas-state</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Armani Guzman celebrates after a base hit against Kansas State" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 18 West Virginia University baseball team completed a sweep of Kansas State with a 13-6 win on Sunday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 31-12 and 16-8 in the Big 12 while the Wildcats fall to 26-22 and 9-15 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg"><media:title>Armani Guzman celebrates after a base hit against Kansas State</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/3/20260502_BASE_WVUvsKansasState_TT-08185.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 3 May 2026 19:05:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59074</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>